CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1952, pg. 20, reads: "In Balmier Days - The Courier camera have preserved for posterity a few scenes from the life of the late genial "Gus" Greenlee, former president of the Negro National League and nationally known sports promoter. At the left, Gus waits his turn to talk during a conference with Satchel Paige (right) and sportswriter Wendell Smith.  He was very active in diamond sport at this time..."
TitMainTitle: Wendell Smith, William "Bill" Nunn Sr., Gus Greenlee, Satchel Paige and another man at a table in Crawford Grill No. 1
